							<div class=3D"qa_answer answer ">
								In this case, your weights add up to 1.75, or 175%. To find your sc=
ore, first add up the individual scores multiplied by their weights: 50(.5)=
 + 70(.5) + 100(.25) + 100(.25) + 7(.25) =3D 111.75. Then, divide the resul=
t by the total weight: 111.75/1.75 =3D 63.86. This means your grade average=
 in the class is 63.86, which you can round up to 64.=20
